abstract: One of the most obvious characteristics of yesterday's market was the apathy of traders and the total lack of any disposition to do business on the past of the average customer in the average brokerage office. abstract: PUNTA ARENAS, Chile, Feb. 7. -- Orders were given by Admiral Evans to-day for his battleships and torpedo boat destroyers to be ready to sail at 11 o'clock tonight. All preparations for their departure were completed to-day. abstract: Just now seems to be a most excellent time for teachers in New York City to keep cool, and especially to keep out of politics. abstract: CHARLOTTE, N.C., Feb. 16. -- While one masked robber held up the cashier in Wild West style, his two companions looted the vault of the bank at Granite Falls, N.C., last night, took all the cash in the institution, $2,700; forced the cashier to enter the vault, locked him in, and made their escape. The robbery was not discovered until 2 o'clock this morning.

abstract: Canada is discovering that it cannot get along without American newspapers. abstract: PALM BEACH, Fla., Feb. 25. -- The annual Scotch foursome at Palm Beach to-day was won by William Anderson, thrice former National open champion, playing with E. abstract: TEHERAN, Persia, Feb. 28. -- An attempt was made in this city this afternoon to assassinate the Shah of Persia with a bomb. On account of a trick practiced with a view to outwitting any plotters he was not hurt. Three outriders who accompanied his automobile, which was running empty, were killed.

abstract: The Friars, an association of advance agents, theatrical men, and newspaper writers, gave a dinner at the Hotel Astor last night in honor of Abraham Lincoln Erlanger. There were 400 persons present. Mr. Erlanger is recognized both by associates and opponents as the dominant figure in the business of American theatrical enterprises, and the dinner in his honor was the occasion for a great reunion of men with various interests in theatre matters.
